    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        " 2.Analyze overfitting and control tree depth"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IsZuLQwxIl6u"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FVs00FpwI20B"
      },
      "execution_count": 49,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Analyze performance with varying max_depth to check for overfitting\n",
        "train_accuracies = []\n",
        "test_accuracies = []\n",
        "depths = range(1, 21)\n",
        "\n",
        "for depth in depths:\n",
        "    clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=depth, random_state=42)\n",
        "    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_pred = clf.predict(X_train)\n",
        "    test_pred = clf.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_accuracies.append(accuracy_score(y_train, train_pred))\n",
        "    test_accuracies.append(accuracy_score(y_test, test_pred))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n56iHdVUHJsb"
      },
      "execution_count": 50,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Plot train and test accuracy vs tree depth\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
        "plt.plot(depths, train_accuracies, label='Train Accuracy', marker='o')\n",
        "plt.plot(depths, test_accuracies, label='Test Accuracy', marker='o')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Max Depth')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.title('Overfitting Analysis: Accuracy vs Tree Depth')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
